Using Kotlin in Intellij IDEA

* Right click your project -> Open Module Settings
* Click on `Libraries` on the left hand side.
* Click the `-` to remove the existing `KotlinJavaRuntime`
* Click the `+` to add a new `Java` library.
* In the path selection screen, enter the following, then choose `Ok`: 
`/opt/m2/repository/org/jetbrains/kotlin/kotlin-stdlib/1.7.20/kotlin-stdlib-1.7.20.jar`
* Click `Apply`, then `Ok` to close the Module settings window.

> problem statements in domejudge (full version) are from the training
> session

This has been fixed.

> Is empty sequence of movements allowed?

Yes
